  <section class="hero" style="padding: 80px 0 40px;">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <h1 class="hero-title" style="font-size: 2.2rem;">Construction Equipment Storage in Vernal, Utah</h1>
      
        <div class="seo-only" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="page-summary-wrap" role="note" aria-label="Business summary">
            <p class="page-summary"><strong>Construction equipment storage in Vernal Utah</strong>. Fort Knox Self Storage offers secure steel containers for tools, building materials, and contractor supplies. 24/7 access, wide driveways for semis. From <strong>$130/month</strong>. <strong>2225 South 3250 East, Vernal, UT 84078</strong>. Call <a href="tel:4358287710">435-828-7710</a>.</p>
            <span class="page-summary-meta">Last updated: <time datetime="2026-04-08">April 2026</time></span>
          </div>
          <div class="voice-answer-block">
            <p><strong>Need construction equipment storage in Vernal?</strong> Fort Knox Self Storage offers 24/7 access steel containers for tools and materials starting at $130 per month. Call James at 435-828-7710.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8;">

        <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
          Contractors and construction crews working in the Uintah Basin need secure, accessible storage for tools, materials, and equipment — especially between projects or during long builds. Fort Knox Self Storage provides heavy-duty steel containers with 24/7 access and driveways wide enough for flatbed trucks, concrete mixers, and equipment trailers.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">Built for Contractors</h2>

        <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 24px;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>All-steel construction.</strong> No one's cutting through a shipping container wall. Four padlock positions per unit for maximum security on high-value tools.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>24/7 access.</strong> Construction schedules don't wait for office hours. Grab materials at 5 AM or drop off tools at midnight.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Semi-truck accessible.</strong> Extra-wide graveled driveways designed for full-size trucks and trailers. No tight corners or cramped aisles.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Dust-proof and mouse-proof.</strong> Fine desert dust and rodents can ruin power tools, electrical components, and wiring. Steel containers keep both out.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>No long-term contract required.</strong> Use it for one project or year-round — month-to-month is fine.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">What Contractors Store at Fort Knox</h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Power tools, hand tools, compressors, generators, ladders, scaffolding components, lumber, drywall, tile, paint, plumbing supplies, electrical supplies, welding equipment, safety gear, and seasonal inventory. A 40ft container at $230/month gives you 320 square feet of fully enclosed, lockable, weather-sealed storage — comparable to a small warehouse bay at a fraction of the cost.</p>

        
